<DESCRIPTION>The Atlas^3D^ sample (E and S0) and spiral galaxies</DESCRIPTION>
<!-- +++No column could be found to attach a LINK in table: J/MNRAS/413/813/atlas3d -->
<DESCRIPTION>Record number assigned by the VizieR team. Should Not be used for identification.</DESCRIPTION>
<!-- {\bf E} for early-type (E and S0) galaxies (Atlas^3D^ sample) or {\bf S} for spiral galaxies (Atlas^3D^ parent sample) -->
<FIELD name="RAJ2000" ucd="pos.eq.ra;meta.main" ref="J2000" datatype="double" width="10" precision="6" unit="deg"><!-- ucd="POS_EQ_RA_MAIN" -->
<FIELD name="DEJ2000" ucd="pos.eq.dec;meta.main" ref="J2000" datatype="double" width="10" precision="6" unit="deg"><!-- ucd="POS_EQ_DEC_MAIN" -->
<DESCRIPTION>[0/2] 1 if the galaxy is in Tonry et al. (2001ApJ...546..681T) and 2 if it is in Mei et al. (2007ApJ...655..144M) or both</DESCRIPTION>
<DESCRIPTION>Number of redshift-independent distance determinations listed in the NED-D catalogue, excluding the ones based on kinematical scaling relations</DESCRIPTION>
<DESCRIPTION>[0/1] 1 if the galaxies is contained within a sphere of radius R=3.5Mpc from the centre of the cluster (1)</DESCRIPTION>
<FIELD name="Vhel" ucd="spect.dopplerVeloc;pos.heliocentric" datatype="short" width="4" unit="km/s"><!-- ucd="VELOC_HC" -->
<FIELD name="Dist" ucd="pos.distance;pos.heliocentric" datatype="float" width="4" precision="1" unit="Mpc"><!-- ucd="POS_GAL_HC" -->
<FIELD name="KMAG" ucd="phys.magAbs;em.IR.K" datatype="float" width="6" precision="2" unit="mag"><!-- ucd="PHOT_ABS-MAG_BAND" -->
<FIELD name="AB" ucd="phys.absorption" datatype="float" width="5" precision="2" unit="mag"><!-- ucd="PHOT_EXTINCTION_ISM" -->
<DESCRIPTION>B-band foreground galactic extinction from Schlegel et al. (1998ApJ...500..525S)</DESCRIPTION>
<FIELD name="T-type" ucd="src.morph.type" datatype="float" width="4" precision="1"><!-- ucd="MORPH_CODE" -->
<FIELD name="log(Re)" ucd="phys.angSize" datatype="float" width="5" precision="2" unit="log(arcsec)"><!-- ucd="EXTENSION_RAD" -->
